sentences: Na Jae-min (Korean: 나재민; born August 13, 2000), known mononymously as Jaemin, is a South Korean rapper, singer, dancer, songwriter and actor.
Na Jaemin was born in Jeonju, South Korea on August 13, 2000.
Jaemin became a trainee under SM Entertainment in 2013, at the age of 13, after being street-cast by staff while handing out posters and collecting trash as a volunteer with his mom at an event.
In 2014, he began to feature in several events of SM Entertainment's pre-debut training team SM Rookies.
From August 2014, he with SM Rookies participated in the SM Town Live World Tour IV.

In October 2014, he made his first broadcast appearance on Exo 90:2014, a reality TV Show, starring labelmate Exo, alongside fellow NCT members, where they get to do dance performances to 90s K-Pop songs.
On April 22, 2015, he was officially announced as a member of SM Rookies.
On July 9, 2015, SM announced that Mark alongside other SM Rookies members will star as Mouseketeers in a Korean revival of The Mickey Mouse Club, which will air on Disney Channel Korea.
